## Flow Control and Position Management

### Pause and Resume

```java
KafkaConsumer<String, String> consumer = new KafkaConsumer<>(props);
consumer.subscribe(Arrays.asList("topic"));

while (running) {
    // Check if worker pool has capacity
    if (workerPool.getQueue().size() > QUEUE_THRESHOLD) {
        // Pause this partition - poll() will not return records from it
        consumer.pause(Arrays.asList(new TopicPartition("topic", 0)));
        System.out.println("Paused partition 0");
    }

    // If resumed, start fetching again
    if (workerPool.getQueue().size() < RESUME_THRESHOLD) {
        consumer.resume(Arrays.asList(new TopicPartition("topic", 0)));
        System.out.println("Resumed partition 0");
    }

    ConsumerRecords<String, String> records = consumer.poll(Duration.ofMillis(100));
    // Paused partitions return no records

    for (ConsumerRecord<String, String> record : records) {
        workerPool.submit(() -> process(record));
    }
}
```

**Pause/Resume Semantics:**

- Paused partitions still participate in fetch requests (heartbeat, metadata)
- Position is maintained but records not returned
- Useful for backpressure without losing offset position
- Does not trigger rebalance
- Can pause/resume different partitions independently

### Position Reset on Rebalance

```java
consumer.subscribe(
    Arrays.asList("topic"),
    new ConsumerRebalanceListener() {
        @Override
        public void onPartitionsAssigned(Collection<TopicPartition> partitions) {
            System.out.println("Assigned: " + partitions);
            // Consumer position is reset (cleared) on assignment

            // Check if we have committed offset
            for (TopicPartition tp : partitions) {
                OffsetAndMetadata committed = consumer.committed(tp);
                if (committed != null) {
                    // Seek to committed offset (resume from last processed)
                    consumer.seek(tp, committed.offset());
                } else {
                    // No committed offset - use auto.offset.reset
                    // - "earliest": seekToBeginning()
                    // - "latest": seekToEnd()
                    // - "none": throw NoOffsetForPartitionException
                }
            }
        }

        @Override
        public void onPartitionsRevoked(Collection<TopicPartition> partitions) {
            // Commit offset before losing partition
            consumer.commitSync();
        }
    }
);
```

### Beginning and End Offset Queries

```java
// Query offsets without seeking
Set<TopicPartition> partitions = consumer.assignment();

// Beginning offsets
Map<TopicPartition, Long> beginning = consumer.beginningOffsets(partitions);
for (TopicPartition tp : partitions) {
    System.out.println(tp + ": earliest=" + beginning.get(tp));
}

// End offsets (high water mark)
Map<TopicPartition, Long> end = consumer.endOffsets(partitions);
for (TopicPartition tp : partitions) {
    System.out.println(tp + ": latest=" + (end.get(tp) - 1));
}

// Safe bounds checking
TopicPartition tp = new TopicPartition("topic", 0);
long beginning = consumer.beginningOffsets(Arrays.asList(tp)).get(tp);
long end = consumer.endOffsets(Arrays.asList(tp)).get(tp);

consumer.seek(tp, Math.max(beginning, Math.min(end - 1, 1000)));
// Seek to offset 1000, but bounded by [beginning, end-1]
```

