## Exception Handling

### Exception Hierarchy

```
Exception
├── WakeupException
│   └── Thrown by poll() when wakeup() called from another thread
│   └── Consumer state still valid, can resume
│
├── CommitFailedException
│   └── Thrown when commit fails due to lost group membership
│   └── Indicates consumer fenced by another group member
│   └── Should exit processing loop and create new consumer
│
├── AuthenticationException / AuthorizationException
│   └── Credentials invalid or lacking permission
│   └── Not retried, should fail fast
│   └── Fix credentials and restart
│
├── IllegalStateException
│   └── Invalid API call sequence
│   └── Examples: subscribe after assign, poll from different thread
│
├── TimeoutException
│   └── Operation exceeded timeout
│   └── May be retried
│   └── Examples: metadata fetch timeout, commit timeout
│
├── OffsetOutOfRangeException
│   └── Requested offset not available in partition
│   └── Offset too old (deleted by retention) or too new
│   └── Seek to valid range and retry
│
├── NoOffsetForPartitionException
│   └── No committed offset and auto.offset.reset=none
│   └── Must explicitly seek to valid offset
│
└── KafkaException (others)
    └── General Kafka errors
    └── Check cause and determine retry strategy
```

### Handling WakeupException

```java
KafkaConsumer<String, String> consumer = new KafkaConsumer<>(props);
consumer.subscribe(Arrays.asList("topic"));

// Shutdown flag from different thread
AtomicBoolean shutdown = new AtomicBoolean(false);

try {
    while (!shutdown.get()) {
        try {
            ConsumerRecords<String, String> records = consumer.poll(Duration.ofSeconds(1));
            for (ConsumerRecord<String, String> record : records) {
                process(record);
            }
        } catch (WakeupException e) {
            // Expected: wakeup() was called
            // Consumer state still valid
            System.out.println("Wakeup signal received");
            // Continue loop to check shutdown flag
        }
    }
} finally {
    consumer.commitSync();  // Final commit
    consumer.close();
}

// Different thread can call wakeup
executorService.submit(() -> {
    Thread.sleep(30000);
    shutdown.set(true);
    consumer.wakeup();  // Interrupt poll()
});
```

### Handling CommitFailedException

```java
while (running) {
    ConsumerRecords<String, String> records = consumer.poll(Duration.ofMillis(100));

    for (ConsumerRecord<String, String> record : records) {
        try {
            processRecord(record);
        } catch (Exception e) {
            System.err.println("Processing failed: " + e);
            // Decide: skip this record or stop consumer
        }
    }

    try {
        consumer.commitSync();
    } catch (CommitFailedException e) {
        // Consumer fenced - another group member now owns partitions
        System.err.println("Consumer fenced: " + e.getMessage());
        System.err.println("This consumer has been removed from group");

        // MUST stop processing and exit
        // Cannot resume with same consumer instance
        // Create new consumer if want to continue
        running = false;
        break;
    } catch (RetriableException e) {
        // Transient error (broker unavailable, timeout, etc.)
        System.err.println("Commit failed (retried): " + e);
        // Will be retried automatically in background
    }
}
```

### Handling OffsetOutOfRangeException

```java
consumer.subscribe(Arrays.asList("topic"));

try {
    while (running) {
        ConsumerRecords<String, String> records = consumer.poll(Duration.ofMillis(100));
        for (ConsumerRecord<String, String> record : records) {
            process(record);
        }
    }
} catch (OffsetOutOfRangeException e) {
    System.err.println("Offset out of range: " + e);
    System.err.println("Probably log deleted or offset too new");

    // Option 1: Reset to earliest
    for (TopicPartition tp : consumer.assignment()) {
        consumer.seekToBeginning(Arrays.asList(tp));
    }

    // Option 2: Reset to latest
    // for (TopicPartition tp : consumer.assignment()) {
    //     consumer.seekToEnd(Arrays.asList(tp));
    // }

    // Option 3: Seek to specific timestamp
    // Long timestamp = System.currentTimeMillis() - 3600000;  // 1 hour ago
    // Map<TopicPartition, Long> timestampMap = ...
    // Map<TopicPartition, OffsetAndTimestamp> offsets = consumer.offsetsForTimes(timestampMap);

    // Continue processing from new position
}
