## Configuration-Driven Behaviors

### Auto Offset Reset Behavior

```java
// auto.offset.reset=earliest (default in many examples)
props.setProperty("auto.offset.reset", "earliest");

// Consumer with no committed offset starts from beginning
consumer.subscribe(Arrays.asList("topic"));
ConsumerRecords<String, String> records = consumer.poll(Duration.ofMillis(100));
// Starts from offset 0 (or log start offset after retention)

// auto.offset.reset=latest
props.setProperty("auto.offset.reset", "latest");
consumer.subscribe(Arrays.asList("topic"));
ConsumerRecords<String, String> records = consumer.poll(Duration.ofMillis(100));
// Starts from current end (skips all existing messages)

// auto.offset.reset=none
props.setProperty("auto.offset.reset", "none");
consumer.subscribe(Arrays.asList("topic"));
ConsumerRecords<String, String> records = consumer.poll(Duration.ofMillis(100));
// Throws: NoOffsetForPartitionException (must seek explicitly)
```

### Isolation Level and Transactional Reads

```java
// isolation.level=read_uncommitted (default)
// - Reads all messages including those in in-flight transactions
// - May read messages that are later aborted
props.setProperty("isolation.level", "read_uncommitted");

ConsumerRecords<String, String> records = consumer.poll(Duration.ofMillis(100));
// Includes all messages: committed and uncommitted

// isolation.level=read_committed
// - Reads only committed/aborted messages
// - Skips messages in in-flight transactions
// - Position stops at Last Stable Offset (LSO)
props.setProperty("isolation.level", "read_committed");

ConsumerRecords<String, String> records = consumer.poll(Duration.ofMillis(100));
// Stops at LSO boundary, in-flight transaction messages skipped

// Example impact:
// Offset sequence: 0, 1, 2 (committed), 3, 4, 5 (in-flight), 6, 7 (committed)
// read_uncommitted: returns all offsets 0-7
// read_committed: returns only 0-2, stops at LSO (offset 5)
```

### Fetch Size and Throughput

```java
// max.poll.records: Maximum records returned per poll()
props.setProperty("max.poll.records", "500");

ConsumerRecords<String, String> records = consumer.poll(Duration.ofMillis(100));
// Returns up to 500 records
// Actual count may be less if fewer available

// fetch.min.bytes: Minimum data before returning
props.setProperty("fetch.min.bytes", "1");      // Return immediately (default)
props.setProperty("fetch.min.bytes", "1024");   // Wait for 1KB of data

// fetch.max.wait.ms: Max time to wait for fetch.min.bytes
props.setProperty("fetch.max.wait.ms", "500");  // Wait up to 500ms

// Impact on poll():
// poll(Duration.ofMillis(100)) with:
// - fetch.min.bytes=1, fetch.max.wait.ms=500: Returns in ~100ms
// - fetch.min.bytes=100000, fetch.max.wait.ms=5000: May wait 5 seconds
```

### Metadata Refresh and Topic Discovery

```java
// metadata.max.age.ms: How often to refresh topic metadata
props.setProperty("metadata.max.age.ms", "300000");  // 5 minutes

// On pattern subscription:
consumer.subscribe(Pattern.compile("logs-.*"));

// On first poll, discovers all matching topics
consumer.poll(Duration.ofMillis(100));

// New topic "logs-new" created
// On next poll after metadata refresh, topic discovered
// If discovered, triggers rebalance on subsequent poll

// Metadata refresh happens every metadata.max.age.ms
// Also triggered on broker errors
```

