## Gotchas and Common Mistakes

### Gotcha 1: Poll Blocks Longer Than Timeout During Rebalance

```java
// Timeout is 100ms, but poll blocks for 5 seconds!
consumer.poll(Duration.ofMillis(100));  // Rebalance happens here
// May block for seconds if rebalance callbacks are slow
```

**Fix:** Be aware rebalances don't respect timeout. Keep callback code fast.

### Gotcha 2: Committed Offset is "Next to Read", Not "Last Read"

```java
ConsumerRecord<String, String> record = records.get(0);
// record.offset() = 42

// To resume from this message:
consumer.seek(partition, 42);  // Wrong! Reads 42 again
consumer.seek(partition, 43);  // Correct! Next offset after 42

// Or in commit:
commitSync(Map.of(partition, new OffsetAndMetadata(43)));  // Not 42!
```

### Gotcha 3: Position Cleared on Rebalance Assignment

```java
consumer.seek(partition, 1000);

// Rebalance happens
// Position is cleared!

// In onPartitionsAssigned:
consumer.seek(partition, 1000);  // Must seek again
```

### Gotcha 4: Callbacks Execute During Poll

```java
long start = System.currentTimeMillis();
consumer.poll(Duration.ofMillis(100));
long elapsed = System.currentTimeMillis() - start;
System.out.println("Actual: " + elapsed + "ms");  // May be seconds!
// Rebalance callbacks run synchronously during poll()
```

### Gotcha 5: Can't Use Same Consumer Instance After Fencing

```java
try {
    consumer.commitSync();
} catch (CommitFailedException e) {
    // Don't continue using this consumer!
    consumer = new KafkaConsumer<>(props);  // Create new instance
}
```

### Gotcha 6: Unsubscribe Requires Poll to Complete

```java
consumer.unsubscribe();  // Just marks for removal
consumer.poll(Duration.ofMillis(100));  // Rebalance happens here
// Now actually unsubscribed
```

### Gotcha 7: Max Poll Interval Includes Processing Time

```java
while (true) {
    ConsumerRecords<String, String> records = consumer.poll(Duration.ofSeconds(10));

    for (ConsumerRecord<String, String> record : records) {
        // If this takes > max.poll.interval.ms total, FENCED!
        processSlowly(record);  // Takes 2 minutes per batch
    }
    // Never polls again within max.poll.interval.ms -> FENCED
}
```

### Gotcha 8: Pattern Subscription Discovers Topics on Metadata Refresh

```java
consumer.subscribe(Pattern.compile("logs-.*"));

// New topic "logs-2024" created
consumer.poll(...);  // May not discover immediately
// Wait for metadata.max.age.ms interval

// To discover faster:
consumer.poll(...);
Thread.sleep(1000);
consumer.poll(...);  // Now discovers new topic
```

